# Pelican UI v2 - Unit Testing Guidelines

Gold standard references:
- `src/pages/bulk-actions/tests/BulkActions.test.tsx`
- `src/pages/bulk-actions/tests/BulkActions.reducer.test.ts`
- `src/pages/bulk-actions/tests/BulkActions.saga.test.ts`

## Stack
- **Framework**: Vitest + Happy DOM
- **UI**: `@testing-library/react`, `@testing-library/user-event`
- **Custom render**: `renderWithProviders` from `~/services/utils/test-utils/renderWithProvider`
- **Mock helpers**: `createAxiosResponse` from `~/shared/common-utils`

## File Structure

Tests live in a `tests/` folder co-located with the feature:

```text
src/pages/<feature>/
├── Feature.tsx
├── Feature.mockData.ts        ← OUTSIDE tests/, shared across all test files
└── tests/
    ├── Feature.test.tsx
    ├── Feature.reducer.test.ts
    ├── Feature.saga.test.ts
    └── components/
        └── SubComponent.test.tsx
```

## Component Tests (`*.test.tsx`)

Reference implementation:
- `src/pages/bulk-actions/tests/BulkActions.test.tsx`
- `src/pages/bulk-actions/tests/bulk-actions-components/CreateMappingModal.test.tsx`
- `src/pages/bulk-actions/tests/bulk-actions-components/ConfigureBulkMapping.test.tsx`

Minimum expected structure:
- Use `renderWithProviders` with feature `preloadedState`.
- Use `beforeEach(() => vi.clearAllMocks())`.
- Use `userEvent.setup()` + `await` for interactions.
- Assert with `getByTestId` / `queryByTestId` first.

### Required test groups per component
- Basic rendering
- Loading state(s)
- Error state(s)
- Data population (one per data variant)
- User interactions (clicks, form input, dispatch checks)
- Conditional rendering (when relevant)

## Reducer Tests (`*.reducer.test.ts`)

Reference implementation:
- `src/pages/bulk-actions/tests/BulkActions.reducer.test.ts`

Minimum expected structure:
- Include unknown action test for initial state.
- Include `*Request`, `*Success`, `*Error` cases for each async slice.
- Assert state shape using `initializeNullState` / `initializeEmptyState` helpers.

### Rules
- Always test initial state with unknown action.
- Write `*Request`, `*Success`, `*Error` tests for every async state slice.
- Test side effects (e.g. a delete success that resets a sibling slice).

## Saga Tests (`*.saga.test.ts`)

Reference implementation:
- `src/pages/bulk-actions/tests/BulkActions.saga.test.ts`

Minimum expected structure:
- Mock service API module.
- Use `afterEach(() => vi.clearAllMocks())`.
- Test both success and error generator flows.
- Validate root saga `all([takeLatest(...)])` wiring.

### Rules
- Test success and error flows for every worker saga.
- Use `generator.throw(axiosError)` to simulate errors.
- `afterEach(() => vi.clearAllMocks())` is mandatory.
- Test the root saga's `all([takeLatest(...)])` structure separately.

## Mock Data (`Feature.mockData.ts`)

Reference implementation:
- `src/pages/bulk-actions/BulkActions.mockData.ts`

Minimum expected structure:
- Export typed entity fixtures.
- Export typed `AxiosError` fixture for saga error tests.
- Export shared state slices (`Loading`, `Success`, `Error`) based on `initializeNullState` or `initializeEmptyState`.

### Rules
- Keep mock data **outside** the `tests/` folder so all test files can import it.
- Provide a typed `AxiosError` mock for every saga test suite.
- Export pre-built state slices (`Loading`, `Success`, `Error`) using `initializeNullState` or `initializeEmptyState` — never inline `{ data: null, isFetching: false, error: null }` objects.
- Use `initializeNullState` for state that holds a single object or `null`; use `initializeEmptyState` for state that holds an array or `[]`.
- Include multiple entity variants when the component renders type-specific UI.

## General Rules
- Use `userEvent.setup()` + `await` for all user interactions.
- Use `vi.clearAllMocks()` in `beforeEach` (component tests) / `afterEach` (saga tests).
- In this codebase, prefer `getByTestId` / `queryByTestId` first for element selection because components expose stable `data-testid` attributes. Production UI should assign `data-testid` on interactive controls (buttons, inputs, selects, form fields) and on major regions you assert in tests so queries stay reliable.
- Use semantic queries (`getByRole`, `getByLabelText`, `getByText`) when validating accessibility behavior, user-visible labels, or when `data-testid` is unavailable.
- Do not test implementation details — assert only what the user or store can observe.
- Avoid `any` types in mock data; use proper interfaces from `*.interface.ts`.

## Running Tests
```bash
yarn test                        # run all
yarn test --watch                # watch mode
yarn test Feature.test.tsx       # single file
yarn test --coverage             # with coverage
```